# Portfolio Website — Setup Guide

## Directory Structure

```
portfolio/
│
├── index.html                ← Single-page layout (Hero, Services, Works, About, Contact)
│
├── css/
│   └── styles.css            ← All styles: dark theme, grid, cards, skeleton, lightbox
│
├── js/
│   ├── supabase-config.js    ← Your Supabase URL + anon key (DO NOT commit to public repo)
│   └── app.js                ← All logic: fetch, filter, lightbox, contact form, stats
│
├── assets/
│   └── images/
│       └── portrait.jpg      ← Your hero portrait photo (420×540px recommended)
│
└── database.sql              ← Full schema — run once in Supabase SQL Editor
```

---

## System Architecture

```
  Browser
    │
    ├── index.html  (structure)
    ├── styles.css  (dark/yellow design system)
    └── app.js      (all logic)
         │
         │  @supabase/supabase-js (CDN)
         │
         ▼
  Supabase (your backend)
    │
    ├── PostgreSQL
    │   ├── designs           (portfolio metadata)
    │   └── contact_messages  (form submissions)
    │
    └── Storage
        └── portfolio-images/ (your image files)
```

---

## Supabase Setup (step by step)

### Step 1 — Create a Supabase project
1. Go to https://supabase.com and sign in
2. Click "New project", fill in name and password
3. Wait ~2 min for provisioning

### Step 2 — Run the SQL schema
1. In your project dashboard, go to **SQL Editor**
2. Paste the entire contents of `database.sql`
3. Click **Run**

### Step 3 — Create the Storage bucket
1. Go to **Storage** → **New bucket**
2. Name: `portfolio-images`
3. Toggle: **Public bucket** → ON
4. Click Create

### Step 4 — Add your credentials
Open `js/supabase-config.js` and replace:

```js
const SUPABASE_URL      = 'https://YOUR_PROJECT_ID.supabase.co';
const SUPABASE_ANON_KEY = 'YOUR_ANON_PUBLIC_KEY';
```

Find these at:
**Dashboard → Settings → API → Project URL + anon/public key**

### Step 5 — Upload your first image
1. Go to **Storage → portfolio-images**
2. Click Upload → select your image file
3. Once uploaded, click the file → **Get URL** → copy the full URL
4. Go to **Table Editor → designs** → Insert row
5. Paste the URL into `image_url`, fill in `title`, `category`, etc.

---

## Adding New Works (ongoing)

For each new design you want to showcase:

1. Upload the image to **Storage → portfolio-images**
2. Copy the public URL
3. Insert a row in the `designs` table:

| Column      | Example value                                      |
|-------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| title       | Jersey No. 7                                       |
| category    | jersey  *(illustration / jersey / branding / other)* |
| description | Custom kit for a basketball team                   |
| image_url   | https://…supabase.co/storage/…/jersey-7.jpg        |
| is_featured | true                                               |
| sort_order  | 1  *(lower = appears first)*                       |

The site fetches live data on every load — no redeploy needed.

---

## Customisation Checklist

- [ ] Replace `YourName` in `index.html` and `styles.css`
- [ ] Add your real email in the contact section of `index.html`
- [ ] Replace `assets/images/portrait.jpg` with your photo
- [ ] Update social media `href="#"` links in the hero
- [ ] Update the hero bio text
- [ ] Replace placeholder stat values with real numbers once you have data
- [ ] Add your real Supabase credentials to `supabase-config.js`

